        <p>Our yearly readings are based on <strong>classical BaZi (Four Pillars)</strong> analysis of the interaction between the year's Heavenly Stem and Earthly Branch (丙午 Bing Wu for 2026) and each animal's inherent branch energy. This is a general guide — for a personalised reading that considers all four pillars of your birth chart, use our <a href="/bazi-calculator/">BaZi Calculator</a>.</p>
        <h3>The 2026 Fire Horse Year</h3>
        <p>2026 is a <strong>Bing Wu (丙午)</strong> year — Heavenly Stem Bing (丙, Yang Fire) sitting atop Earthly Branch Wu (午, Horse/Fire). This is a double-fire combination, making it one of the most intensely Yang years in the sexagenary cycle. The last Fire Horse year was 1966. Fire Horse years are associated with bold action, dramatic change, passionate energy, and volatility.</p>
        <p>The dominant <a href="/wuxing/">Fire element</a> in 2026 means that animals with strong Water or Metal in their nature may face challenges from the controlling cycle, while Wood animals receive generous support from the generating cycle. Earth animals benefit from Fire's productive energy, and fellow Fire animals experience both amplification and competition.</p>
